x4freetext: Tc-95 is Produced at Higher Energies Via Both a (D,N)
And (D,2N)-Reaction. From a Comparison with Low-Energy
Data (SEE SUBENTRY B0109010),Which Contain Only the
(D,N)-Reaction,the Compiler Concluded That the Present
Data are not Related to Natural Isotopic Abundances But
Were Normalized to the Sum of the Isotopic Abundances
Of Mo-94 and Mo-95, from Which Tc-95 can be Produced.
Thus, For Correct Renormalization, the Data Should
Probably be Multiplied with the Sum of the Abundances
Of Both Target Isotopes (COMMENT BY THE COMPILER OF
KACHAPAG)

x4freetext: The Thick Target Yield was Calculated by Integrating
The Differential Cross Sections Measured from a Stack
As Given in Subentries B0109002 to B0109008 After
Renormalization to Natural Isotopic Abundances.
Saturation Production Rates in Microcurie/Microampere
Were Calculated on the Basis of the Cross Sections
Given.
The Thick Target Yield Given is Too High Compared
With the Saturation Production Rate of 3493 Microcurie/
Microampere at 11.7 MeV Calculated by the Authors. The
Correct Thick Target Yield Should be Lower Than this
Value. The Discrepancy to the Value Given is Due to the
Fact That a Formula was Used Which is Valid Only For
Irradiation Times Short in Respect to the Half-Life
(COMMENT BY THE COMPILER OF KACHAPAG)
This Value Supersedes Data Published Earlier by
The Authors (ISOTOPENPRAXIS,5,247,1969, SEE ALSO ENTRY
B0084). The Difference to the Former Value is Probably
Due to a Less Accurate Beam Current Determination.
